atmIfTable.name: atmIfTable
atmIfTable.description: The atmIfTable displays all available ATM capable interfaces.

atmIfEntry.name: atmIfEntry
atmIfEntry.description: An interface entry containing objects at the subnetwork layer and below for a particular interface.

atmIfIndex.name: atmIfIndex
atmIfIndex.description: The interface index of the associated ATM hardware.

atmIfType.name: atmIfType
atmIfType.description: This object contains an interface type.

atmIfAdminStatus.name: atmIfAdminStatus
atmIfAdminStatus.description: This object contains the desired state of the ATM interface.

atmIfOperStatus.name: atmIfOperStatus
atmIfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the ATM interface.

atmIfLastChange.name: atmIfLastChange
atmIfLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the interface entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

atmIfMaxTxRate.name: atmIfMaxTxRate
atmIfMaxTxRate.description: This object enables traffic shaping on the related ATM interface. If set to zero (0) there is no shaping active. Otherwise this variable defines the maximum amount of bits per second to be transmitted. Note that the maximum transmit rate is also determined by the capabilities of the ATM hardware.

atmIfOperMode.name: atmIfOperMode
atmIfOperMode.description: The current operational mode of the ATM interface. The value atm(1) means ATM is used on the line. The value efm(2) means ATM is used only internally and Ethernet with HDLC framing is used on the line.

atmIfInPkts.name: atmIfInPkts
atmIfInPkts.description: The number of reassembled received packets.

atmIfRxSpeed.name: atmIfRxSpeed
atmIfRxSpeed.description: This object contains the receive interface speed.

atmIfTxSpeed.name: atmIfTxSpeed
atmIfTxSpeed.description: This object contains the transmit interface speed.

atmIfInOctets.name: atmIfInOctets
atmIfInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

atmIfInDiscards.name: atmIfInDiscards
atmIfInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

atmIfInErrors.name: atmIfInErrors
atmIfInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

atmIfOutOctets.name: atmIfOutOctets
atmIfOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

atmIfOutDiscards.name: atmIfOutDiscards
atmIfOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

atmIfOutErrors.name: atmIfOutErrors
atmIfOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

atmVpcTable.name: atmVpcTable
atmVpcTable.description: A table of status and parameter information on the virtual path connections which cross this UNI. There is one entry in this table for each permanent virtual path connection. This is the lite version of ATM-FORUM-MIB DEFINITIONS

atmVpcEntry.name: atmVpcEntry
atmVpcEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a particular virtual path connection.

atmVpcPortIndex.name: atmVpcPortIndex
atmVpcPortIndex.description: The interface index of the associated ATM hardware.

atmVpcVpi.name: atmVpcVpi
atmVpcVpi.description: The VPI value of this Virtual Path Connection.

atmVpcOperStatus.name: atmVpcOperStatus
atmVpcOperStatus.description: The present actual operational status of the VPC. A value of end2endUp(2) or end2endDown(3) would be used if the end-to-end status is known. If only local status information is available, a value of localUpEnd2endUnknown(4) or localDown(5) would be used.

atmVccTable.name: atmVccTable
atmVccTable.description: A table of status and parameter information on the virtual channel connections which are visible at this UNI. There is one entry in this table for each permanent virtual channel connection, including reserved VCCs that are supported; e.g., signalling, OAM flows, and ILMI, but not unassigned cells. This is the lite version of ATM-FORUM-MIB DEFINITIONS

atmVccEntry.name: atmVccEntry
atmVccEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a particular virtual channel connection.

atmVccPortIndex.name: atmVccPortIndex
atmVccPortIndex.description: The interface index of the associated ATM hardware.

atmVccVpi.name: atmVccVpi
atmVccVpi.description: The VPI value of this Virtual Channel Connection.

atmVccVci.name: atmVccVci
atmVccVci.description: The VCI value of this Virtual Channel Connection.

atmVccOperStatus.name: atmVccOperStatus
atmVccOperStatus.description: The present actual operational status of the VCC. A value of end2endUp(2) or end2endUp(3) is used if the end-to-end status is known. If only local status is known a value of localUpEnd2endUnknown(4) or localDown(5) is used.

atmOamTable.name: atmOamTable
atmOamTable.description: This tables contains all OAM configuration parameters.

atmOamAtmIfIndex.name: atmOamAtmIfIndex
atmOamAtmIfIndex.description: The interface index of the associated ATM hardware.

atmOamVpi.name: atmOamVpi
atmOamVpi.description: The VPI value of this Virtual Path/Channel Connection.

atmOamVci.name: atmOamVci
atmOamVci.description: The VCI value of this Virtual Channel Connection.

atmOamFlowLevel.name: atmOamFlowLevel
atmOamFlowLevel.description: The OAM hierarchical flow levels : VC (F5) or VP (F4).

atmOamLoopbackEnd2End.name: atmOamLoopbackEnd2End
atmOamLoopbackEnd2End.description: Indicates wether OAM loopback is enabled onto the end-to-end connection.

atmOamLoopbackSegment.name: atmOamLoopbackSegment
atmOamLoopbackSegment.description: Indicates wether active OAM loopback is enabled onto the segment connection.

atmOamLoopbackEnd2EndInterval.name: atmOamLoopbackEnd2EndInterval
atmOamLoopbackEnd2EndInterval.description: OAM loopback transmit interval (in seconds) for end-to-end context.

atmOamLoopbackSegmentInterval.name: atmOamLoopbackSegmentInterval
atmOamLoopbackSegmentInterval.description: OAM loopback transmit interval (in seconds) for segment context.

atmOamLoopbackEnd2EndMaxPending.name: atmOamLoopbackEnd2EndMaxPending
atmOamLoopbackEnd2EndMaxPending.description: Specifies the maximum number of outstanding OAM loopback responses after which the associated F4/F5 instance will be set into the end-to-end operational down status.

atmOamLoopbackSegmentMaxPending.name: atmOamLoopbackSegmentMaxPending
atmOamLoopbackSegmentMaxPending.description: Specifies the maximum number of outstanding OAM loopback responses after which the associated F4/F5 instance will be set into the segment operational down status.

atmOamCCEnd2EndActivation.name: atmOamCCEnd2EndActivation
atmOamCCEnd2EndActivation.description: Determines wether OAM continuity check activation request will be activated and/or accepted for the associated end-to-end connection. If set to passive(1) or both(3) CC activation requests will be confirmed. If set to active(2) or both CC will be requested. If set to no-negotiation(4) - depending on the settings in atmOamCCEnd2EndDirection - CC cells will be send and/or expected periodically without any previous CC activation negotiation. If set to none(5) neither CC activation will be requested/confirmed nor any CC cells will be generated/expected.

atmOamCCSegmentActivation.name: atmOamCCSegmentActivation
atmOamCCSegmentActivation.description: Determines wether OAM continuity check activation request will be activated and/or accepted for the associated segment connection. If set to passive(1) or both(3) CC activation requests will be confirmed. If set to active(2) or both CC will be requested. If set to no-negotiation(4) - depending on the settings in atmOamCCSegmentDirection - CC cells will be send and/or expected periodically without any previous CC activation negotiation. If set to none(5) neither CC activation will be requested/confirmed nor any CC cells will be generated/expected.

atmOamCCEnd2EndDirection.name: atmOamCCEnd2EndDirection
atmOamCCEnd2EndDirection.description: Determines OAM continuity check direction (for end-to-end). If set to sink(1) CC cells will be received only, if set to source(2) CC cells will be generated periodically, if set to both(3) CC cells will be received from the source as well as send to the sink.

atmOamCCSegmentDirection.name: atmOamCCSegmentDirection
atmOamCCSegmentDirection.description: Determines OAM continuity check direction (for segment). If set to sink(1) CC cells will be received only, if set to source(2) CC cells will be generated periodically, if set to both(3) CC cells will be received from the source as well as send to the sink.

atmOamStatTable.name: atmOamStatTable
atmOamStatTable.description: This tables displays all used VCs.

atmOamStatAtmIfIndex.name: atmOamStatAtmIfIndex
atmOamStatAtmIfIndex.description: The interface index of the associated ATM hardware.

atmOamStatVpi.name: atmOamStatVpi
atmOamStatVpi.description: The VPI value of this Virtual Path Connection.

atmOamStatVci.name: atmOamStatVci
atmOamStatVci.description: The VCI value of this Virtual Channel Connection.

atmOamStatFlowType.name: atmOamStatFlowType
atmOamStatFlowType.description: The OAM hierarchical flow levels: see ITU I.610

atmOamStatLoopbackTxCells.name: atmOamStatLoopbackTxCells
atmOamStatLoopbackTxCells.description: The number of OAM loopback cells that have been sent to the target in this sequence.

atmOamStatLoopbackRxCells.name: atmOamStatLoopbackRxCells
atmOamStatLoopbackRxCells.description: The number of OAM loopback cells that have been received from the target in this sequence.

atmOamStatLoopbackPending.name: atmOamStatLoopbackPending
atmOamStatLoopbackPending.description: The number of currently outstanding OAM loopback responses.

atmOamStatLoopbackCorr.name: atmOamStatLoopbackCorr
atmOamStatLoopbackCorr.description: The correlation of the last sent loopback message.

atmOamStatAisState.name: atmOamStatAisState
atmOamStatAisState.description: The AIS state is set to on(2) after receiving an AIS cell or detection of LOC (Loss of Continuity). The Ais state is set to off(1) either when receiving user cells (same VCC context) or via timeout.

atmOamStatAisTxCells.name: atmOamStatAisTxCells
atmOamStatAisTxCells.description: The number of OAM alarm indication signal (AIS) cells that have been transmitted since last change of AisState.

atmOamStatAisRxCells.name: atmOamStatAisRxCells
atmOamStatAisRxCells.description: The number of OAM alarm indication signal (AIS) cells that have been received since last change of AisState.

atmOamStatTotalAisTxCells.name: atmOamStatTotalAisTxCells
atmOamStatTotalAisTxCells.description: The total number of OAM alarm indication signal (AIS) cells that have been transmitted.

atmOamStatTotalAisRxCells.name: atmOamStatTotalAisRxCells
atmOamStatTotalAisRxCells.description: The total number of OAM alarm indication signal (AIS) cells that have been received.

atmOamStatRdiState.name: atmOamStatRdiState
atmOamStatRdiState.description: The RDI state is set to on(2) after receiving a RDI cell. The RDI state is to off(1) via timeout.

atmOamStatRdiTxCells.name: atmOamStatRdiTxCells
atmOamStatRdiTxCells.description: The number of OAM remote defect indication (RDI) cells that have been transmitted since last change of RdiState.

atmOamStatRdiRxCells.name: atmOamStatRdiRxCells
atmOamStatRdiRxCells.description: The number of OAM remote defect indication (RDI) cells that have been received since last change of RdiState.

atmOamStatTotalRdiTxCells.name: atmOamStatTotalRdiTxCells
atmOamStatTotalRdiTxCells.description: The totoal number of OAM remote defect indication (RDI) cells that have been transmitted.

atmOamStatTotalRdiRxCells.name: atmOamStatTotalRdiRxCells
atmOamStatTotalRdiRxCells.description: The total number of OAM remote defect indication (RDI) cells that have been received.

atmOamStatCCActivatorState.name: atmOamStatCCActivatorState
atmOamStatCCActivatorState.description: The status of the initiated CC negotiation, inactive(1) is the initial status, wait-act-con(2) is set after sending an CC activation request, active(3) is reached after receiving the CC activation confirmation whereas wait-deact-con(4) is used to indicate awaiting the CC deactivation confirmation.

atmOamStatCCActivatorDirection.name: atmOamStatCCActivatorDirection
atmOamStatCCActivatorDirection.description: The direction of action indicated by a received CC activation confirmation, source(1) correlates with 'A-B', sink(2) with 'B-A' and both(3) with 'A-B' and 'B-A'.

atmOamStatCCActivatorCorr.name: atmOamStatCCActivatorCorr
atmOamStatCCActivatorCorr.description: The correlation of the last CC activation message sent to the responder.

atmOamStatCCResponderState.name: atmOamStatCCResponderState
atmOamStatCCResponderState.description: The status of the passive CC negotiation, inactive(1) is the initial status, active(3) is reached after receiving an CC activation request whereas wait-deact-con(4) is used to indicate awaiting the CC deactivation confirmation.

atmOamStatCCResponderDirection.name: atmOamStatCCResponderDirection
atmOamStatCCResponderDirection.description: The direction of action indicated by a received CC activation request, source(1) correlates with 'B-A', sink(2) with 'A-B' and both(3) with 'A-B' and 'B-A'.

atmOamStatCCResponderCorr.name: atmOamStatCCResponderCorr
atmOamStatCCResponderCorr.description: The correlation of the received CC activation message.

atmOamStatCCTxCells.name: atmOamStatCCTxCells
atmOamStatCCTxCells.description: The number of OAM continuity check cells that have been sent to the target in this sequence.

atmOamStatCCRxCells.name: atmOamStatCCRxCells
atmOamStatCCRxCells.description: The number of OAM continuity check cells that have been received from the target in this sequence.

ethoaPvcTable.name: ethoaPvcTable
ethoaPvcTable.description: The ethoaPvcTable displays all virtual ethernets defined for a VCI/VPI on a specified hardware.

ethoaPvcIfIndex.name: ethoaPvcIfIndex
ethoaPvcIfIndex.description: This object contains an interface index and assigns the row to an entry in ifTable. When creating new entries in the table, the value of this object shall be set to 0. The next free ifIndex value is than allocated and assigned to the object. At the same time a new interface is created in the IfTable.

ethoaPvcDescr.name: ethoaPvcDescr
ethoaPvcDescr.description: Short description of the configured PVC

ethoaPvcAtmIfIndex.name: ethoaPvcAtmIfIndex
ethoaPvcAtmIfIndex.description: The Index to the ATM hardware.

ethoaPvcVpi.name: ethoaPvcVpi
ethoaPvcVpi.description: The VPI value of this Virtual Path Connection.

ethoaPvcVci.name: ethoaPvcVci
ethoaPvcVci.description: The VCI value of this Virtual Channel Connection.

ethoaPvcEncapsulation.name: ethoaPvcEncapsulation
ethoaPvcEncapsulation.description: This values decides whether frames are send without FCS(1), with FCS(2) or wether VC multiplexing is used.

ethoaPvcPhysAddress.name: ethoaPvcPhysAddress
ethoaPvcPhysAddress.description: The MAC-Address used for the virtual interface.

rpoaPvcTable.name: rpoaPvcTable
rpoaPvcTable.description: This table configures Vpi/Vci for raw protocols (IP, IPX, etc.)

rpoaPvcIfIndex.name: rpoaPvcIfIndex
rpoaPvcIfIndex.description: This object contains an interface index and assigns the row to an entry in ifTable. When creating new entries in the table, the value of this object shall be set to 0. The next free ifIndex value is than allocated and assigned to the object. At the same time a new interface is created in the IfTable.

rpoaPvcDescr.name: rpoaPvcDescr
rpoaPvcDescr.description: Short description of the configured PVC

rpoaPvcAtmIfIndex.name: rpoaPvcAtmIfIndex
rpoaPvcAtmIfIndex.description: The Index to the ATM hardware.

rpoaPvcVpi.name: rpoaPvcVpi
rpoaPvcVpi.description: The VPI value of this Virtual Path Connection.

rpoaPvcVci.name: rpoaPvcVci
rpoaPvcVci.description: The VCI value of this Virtual Channel Connection.

rpoaPvcEncapsulation.name: rpoaPvcEncapsulation
rpoaPvcEncapsulation.description: This values decides whether frames are send codes with LLC 0xAA 0xAA (non-ISO), LLC 0xFE 0xFE (ISO) or wether VC multiplexing is used.

pppoaPvcTable.name: pppoaPvcTable
pppoaPvcTable.description: This table configures Vpi/Vci for PPP oaver AAL5 (PPPoA) permanent and on-demand sessions.

pppoaPvcIfIndex.name: pppoaPvcIfIndex
pppoaPvcIfIndex.description: This object contains an interface index and refers to an entry in ifTable. When creating new entries in the table, the next free ifIndex value is than allocated and assigned to the object. At the same time a new interface is created in the IfTable with that very index.

pppoaPvcDescr.name: pppoaPvcDescr
pppoaPvcDescr.description: Short description of the configured PVC

pppoaPvcAtmIfIndex.name: pppoaPvcAtmIfIndex
pppoaPvcAtmIfIndex.description: The Index to the ATM hardware.

pppoaPvcVpi.name: pppoaPvcVpi
pppoaPvcVpi.description: The VPI value of this Virtual Path Connection.

pppoaPvcVci.name: pppoaPvcVci
pppoaPvcVci.description: The VCI value of this Virtual Channel Connection.

pppoaPvcEncapsulation.name: pppoaPvcEncapsulation
pppoaPvcEncapsulation.description: This value decides whether VC multiplexing or LLC encapsulation is used.

pppoaPvcClientType.name: pppoaPvcClientType
pppoaPvcClientType.description: This variable defines whether the PPP over AAL5 session will be established permanent(1) or initiated on-demand(2).

atmQosVccTable.description: This table provides QoS information for each active ATM VC on the related ATM interface

atmQosVccEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing ATM QoS parameters about a particular virtual connection.

atmQosVccAtmIfIndex.name: atmQosVccAtmIfIndex
atmQosVccAtmIfIndex.description: The interface index of the associated ATM hardware.

atmQosVccVci.description: The VCI value of this Virtual Channel Connection.

atmQosVccService.name: atmQosVccService
atmQosVccService.description: The ATM service category of this virtual circuit connection: cbr vbr vbr2 vbr3 VBR1 + Best Effort vbr-rt real-time vbr2-rt real-time vbr3-rt real-time ubr Best Effort ubr2 Best Effort abr delete

atmQosVccOutMcr.name: atmQosVccOutMcr
atmQosVccOutMcr.description: Output Minimum Cell Rate (MCR) in bps for connection with vbr-nrt(3).

atmAtucPerfPrev1DayDataCells.name: atmAtucPerfPrev1DayDataCells
